Take him!

50:45.834 --> 50:47.210
You cannot win this!

50:52.216 --> 50:55.299
Stay, and see vengeance
forever denied.

51:10.276 --> 51:12.892
You are no better than Rhaskos
and the fucking Gauls.

51:13.070 --> 51:16.028
All driven
only by your own desires.

51:16.198 --> 51:18.940
Do any of us hold
fucking worth to you?

51:19.118 --> 51:20.574
The reason I went alone.

51:20.744 --> 51:24.202
A hard comfort, if you had
fallen to Glaber's men.

51:24.373 --> 51:25.829
Agron would have led you south.

51:26.000 --> 51:27.115
We need a leader,

51:27.293 --> 51:30.205
not some angry boy
who can barely piss

51:30.379 --> 51:31.835
without splashing
everyone about him.

51:32.006 --> 51:33.587
What would you have me do?

51:33.757 --> 51:38.046
Turn from the man that condemned
my wife to slavery?

51:38.220 --> 51:41.053
Let him live,

51:41.223 --> 51:44.386
that took everything from me?

51:49.690 --> 51:53.057
Your heart still beats.

51:53.235 --> 51:56.102
Place ear to chest,

51:56.280 --> 51:59.067
and you will find it
absent sound.

52:01.118 --> 52:03.951
And yet you are not dead.

52:06.707 --> 52:08.322
Because of you.

52:08.500 --> 52:10.627
Know that you have my gratitude.

52:13.213 --> 52:15.124
I didn't come to lend you aid,
you mad fuck.

52:15.299 --> 52:17.255
-(coughs)
- I came to stop you.

52:20.554 --> 52:23.887
You would place yourself between
Glaber and what he deserves?

52:24.058 --> 52:28.347
As you would place yourself
between Naevia and me.

52:30.189 --> 52:32.521
What do you think
would be the result

52:32.691 --> 52:36.149
of killing a fucking praetor?

52:36.320 --> 52:38.231
The Senate would burn upon itself,

52:38.405 --> 52:41.112
belching forth fire and vengeance.

52:41.283 --> 52:43.865
They would not send a few men,
as they do with Glaber.

52:44.036 --> 52:45.242
They would send thousands,

52:45.412 --> 52:47.403
a true army...

52:48.957 --> 52:50.788
which we will never be.

52:54.380 --> 52:56.792
( footsteps )

52:58.967 --> 53:01.253
Aurelia calls for you.

53:18.487 --> 53:20.648
(gasping )

53:22.199 --> 53:23.405
Spartacus.

53:23.575 --> 53:26.032
I am here.

53:30.124 --> 53:31.330
Promise me...

53:31.500 --> 53:33.331
Anything.

53:35.421 --> 53:36.877
Promise...

53:37.047 --> 53:39.254
you will stay far from my son.

53:42.261 --> 53:45.253
I would not have him die
in your wake...

53:47.099 --> 53:49.431
as his father

53:49.601 --> 53:51.341
and mother.

54:25.846 --> 54:29.134
Glaber and his men
will pay in blood.

54:30.350 --> 54:31.851
Gather swords.

54:32.019 --> 54:33.600
No.

54:37.065 --> 54:38.441
We move south...

54:41.278 --> 54:42.939
to find Naevia.

54:44.072 --> 54:47.235
Let Crixus and the other Gauls
chase lost hope.

54:47.409 --> 54:49.525
- Spartacus--
- The decision's been made.

54:52.790 --> 54:54.826
We must stand as one...

54:58.378 --> 55:01.745
or fall divided.

55:07.304 --> 55:09.966
A lesson hard learned.

55:11.642 --> 55:13.178
Shackle will be struck

55:13.352 --> 55:15.968
from every slave
upon our path.

55:16.146 --> 55:19.513
We will see
our numbers grow,

55:19.691 --> 55:23.183
and when they
have become legion,

55:23.362 --> 55:25.569
we will face Glaber

55:25.739 --> 55:29.072
and the hordes of Rome again,

55:29.243 --> 55:32.235
and the gods shall weep
for their suffering.
